# PR Conflict Resolver — mandatory (governance merge conflicts)

**Law:** `brain-os/law/enforcement/PR_CONFLICT_RESOLVER_MANDATORY_LOCKED_v1.md`  
**Skill:** `~/Desktop/Noetfield-Systems/sina-governance-SSOT/skills/pr-conflict-resolver/SKILL.md`  
**Eval app:** `~/Desktop/PR-Conflict-Resolver-Report.app`  
**SSOT:** `data/pr-conflict-resolver-mandatory-v1.json`

## Hard rule

> Before resolving any governance-sensitive merge conflict — read skill, classify files, ack first-check. **Never** blind-pick registry JSON or LOCKED docs.

## Before conflict resolution

```bash
python3 scripts/pr_conflict_resolver_first_check_v1.py --wire --json
python3 scripts/pr_conflict_resolver_first_check_v1.py --ack --json
```

Read SG skill §0–§5. Open eval app if changing skill law.

## Machine gates

| Gate | Blocks |
|---|---|
| `pre_write_guard_v1.py` | Conflict markers on governance paths without ack |
| `pr_conflict_resolver_first_check_v1.py --check` | Merge + sensitive path without ack |
| `validate-pr-conflict-resolver-mandatory-v1.sh` | Missing wiring |

## Stop and escalate (skill §3)

- LOCKED ssot conflict
- Same `task_cell` / registry key, different owners
- Merge-ready claim without resolution receipt

## After resolve

```bash
bash scripts/validate-pr-conflict-resolver-mandatory-v1.sh
```

Write `receipts/pr-conflict-resolution-<UTC>.json` — files, class, validators, open questions.
